{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πίναξ</b> [ῐ], ᾰκος, ὁ, <br /> <b>board, plank</b>, πίνακάς τε νεῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.67; εὐγόμφοισιν.. πινάκεσσιν 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 1.194 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], compare πινακηδό; πίνακος κουρά sawdust, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus: hence of things made of flat wood, metal, etc., \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> <b>drawing</b>- or <b>writing-tablet</b>, ={δέλτος}, γράψας ἐν π. πτυκτῷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.169; πίναξιν.. ἐγγεγραμμένα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 946; πινάκων ξεστῶν δέλτοι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 778; ἐν χρυσῷ π. γράψαντες 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 120c, compare “R.” 501a \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of a <b>votive tablet</b> hung on the image of a god, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 463, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1341a36, “IG” 42(1).121.24(Epid., 4th c.BC, _plural_), 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 4.19, 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 8.6.15 (_plural_), etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Πίνακες <b>tables</b> or <b>catalogues</b> of authors, name of a work by Callimachus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 8.86, compare 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 6.244a, 13.585b, 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus see {Καλλίμαχος}\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>lists</b> of philosophers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Sulla” 26; αἵ τ᾽ ἀναγραφαὶ τῶν π. αἵ τε βυβλιοθῆκαι 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ τῶν Στωικῶν” 339.13. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>trencher, platter</b>, κρειῶν πίνακας παρέθηκεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.141, compare 16.49 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ἀργυροῦ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philippides Comicus 9.4; π. χαλκοῦς 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 4.128d \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>salver</b>, πίνακα.. μέγαν, ἔχοντα μικροὺς πέντε πινακίσκους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Lynceus Comicus 1.5, compare 17, 19 \">Refs</a>]; πίνακες ὑέλινοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 7.106. \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>board</b> for painting on, <b>picture</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 178, 4th c.BC: Anaxandrides Comicus 33.2; π. οἱ γραφόμενοι 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 5.7.4, compare “IG” 11(2).161 A 75 (Delos, 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> generally, <b>plate with anything drawn</b> or <b>engraved on it</b>, χάλκεος π., of a map, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.49, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Theseus” 1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. γεωγραφικός, first made by Anaximander, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 1.1.11. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>board</b> or <b>tablet</b> on which astronomical tables were drawn, ἡ περὶ πίνακα μέθοδος the art of casting nativities, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Romulus” 12 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ἀγυρτικοὶ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Comp. Arist.Cat.” 3, compare πινάκιον 11.3. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__5.b</b></Level4> proverbial, ἐκ πίνακος καὶ πυλαίας, of a trivial fiction, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.386b. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>public notice-board</b> or <b>register</b>, π. ἐκκλησιαστικός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 44.35, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; but δαμόσιος π. public <b>archive</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 671 A 15 (Delph., 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> <b>strop</b>, to sharpen knives on, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 5.5.1. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__8</b></Level3> <b>toy-theatre</b> for marionettes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “Automatopoetica” 23.1, +others\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] (Cf. OSlavonic <i>p[icaron]n[icaron]</i> 'tree-stump'.)","strongNumber":"G4094","accentedUnicode":"πίναξ","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4093","matchingForm":"πινακίδιον","stepTransliteration":"pinakidion","gloss":"little tablet","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一塊寫字板","_es_Gloss":"tabla pequeña","_zh_Gloss":"一块写字板"},{"strongNumber":"G4109","matchingForm":"πλάξ","stepTransliteration":"plax","gloss":"tablet","_zh_tw_Gloss":"版","_es_Gloss":"tabla","_zh_Gloss":"版"}],"shortDef":"platter, dish","mediumDef":"<i>primarily</i> <b>a board</b> or <b>plank;</b> in NT <b>a plate, platter, dish</b> on which food was served, <ref='Mrk.14.8, 11'>Mk. 14:8, 11</ref>","stepGloss":"platter","stepTransliteration":"pinax","count":5,"_es_Definition":"plato, bandeja, plato grande","_zh_tw_Definition":"大淺盤","_zh_Definition":"大浅盘","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"mâm; cái khay. Xem G4109","_zh_tw_Gloss":"盤子","_es_Gloss":"plato","_zh_Gloss":"盘子"}]}